<item>
            <title>[DATAMONGO-862] Update Array Field Using Positional Operator ($) Does Not Work</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-862</link>
                <project id="10701" key="DATAMONGO">Spring Data MongoDB</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After updating to a newer version of Spring Data MongoDB, I found that I can no longer update array fields. The most recent version I observed this to work correctly is 1.2.x.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In 1.3.x and above, it seems that the positional operator ($) is removed from the key.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example:&lt;br/&gt;
mongoOps.findAndModify(new Query(), new Update().set(&quot;options.$.name&quot;, &quot;color&quot;), MongoProduct.class);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the actual command, &quot;options.$.name&quot; turns into &quot;options.name&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This results in the mongodb error: &quot;exception: can&apos;t append to array using string field name: name&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>mongodb 2.4.4, os x mavericks</environment>
